          <p class="book-info__copy__description-content">"Meditations" is a collection of personal reflections and philosophical insights written by Marcus Aurelius, a Roman Emperor and Stoic philosopher, during his reign from 161 to 180 AD. In this timeless work, Marcus Aurelius shares his thoughts on virtue, resilience, and the pursuit of inner peace in the face of life's challenges. Written as a series of notes to himself, "Meditations" offers readers practical wisdom and guidance for living a meaningful and ethical life. Marcus Aurelius reflects on themes such as the importance of self-discipline, the transient nature of life, and the power of reason and mindfulness.</p>
